**Step-by-step calculation:**

1. **Return on Equity (ROE):**
   \[
   \text{ROE} = \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Average Equity}}
   \]
   - Net Profit = 146,127.58
   - Beginning Equity = 16,000,000.00
   - Ending Equity = 16,146,127.58
   - Average Equity = (16,000,000.00 + 16,146,127.58) / 2 = 16,073,063.79

   Thus:
   \[
   \text{ROE} = \frac{146,127.58}{16,073,063.79} \approx 0.009096 = 0.91\%
   \]

2. **Debt to Asset Ratio:**
   \[
   \text{Debt to Asset Ratio} = \frac{\text{Total Liabilities}}{\text{Total Assets}}
   \]
   - Total Liabilities (End of period) = 5,515,978.61
   - Total Assets (End of period) = 21,662,106.19

   \[
   \text{Debt to Asset Ratio} = \frac{5,515,978.61}{21,662,106.19} \approx 0.2547 \approx 0.25
   \]

3. **Gross Profit Margin:**
   \[
   \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Revenue}}
   \]
   - Gross Profit = 300,421.65
   - Revenue = 863,371.65

   \[
   \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \frac{300,421.65}{863,371.65} \approx 0.3481 = 34.81\%
   \]
